{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013sPQYxTAqY1XJnKHviFZro","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the full contents of the referral migration file showing the exact table schema:\n\n## `referral_codes` Table\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS referral_codes (\n  id              SERIAL       PRIMARY KEY,\n  wallet          TEXT         NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  code            TEXT         NOT NULL UNIQUE,  -- player-chosen, 3-16 chars [a-z0-9-]\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**Key properties:**\n- `wallet` is UNIQUE — one active code per wallet\n- `code` is UNIQUE and player-chosen, 3-16 character range with allowed pattern `[a-z0-9-]`\n- Both `created_at` and `updated_at` have default `now()` \n- No indexes defined on this table itself\n\n---\n\n## Related Tables (for reference)\n\nThe migration also defines four related tables you'll likely need DB client methods for:\n\n1. **`referral_links`** — immutable referrer→referee binding (one per player)\n   - Index on `referrer_wallet` for looking up referees by referrer\n\n2. **`referral_earnings`** — per-game earnings tracking with idempotency guard via `UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)`\n   - Indexes on `referrer_wallet`, `referee_wallet`, and `round_id`\n\n3. **`referral_claims`** — async SOL payout tracking with status lifecycle (pending → processing → completed/failed)\n   - Indexes on `wallet` and filtered status index for pending/processing\n\n4. **`referral_kol_rates`** — KOL custom referrer rate overrides (one row per KOL wallet)\n   - No indexes beyond primary key\n\nThis is the complete schema that your DB client methods will need to interface with."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a394597d6cc07e095 (use SendMessage with to: 'a394597d6cc07e095' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 37372\ntool_uses: 1\nduration_ms: 7838</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use