all methods\n- Initializes postgres connection pool internally:\n```typescript\nexport function createDb(databaseUrl: string): Db {\n  const sql = postgres(databaseUrl);\n  return {\n    // method implementations\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Method Signatures (Return Types)\nAll methods are **async functions** returning `Promise<T>`:\n- **Insert methods**: `Promise<RoundType>` or `Promise<void>` (batch inserts)\n- **Get/Read methods**: `Promise<Type | undefined>` (single) or `Promise<Type[]>` (list)\n- **Update methods**: `Promise<Type>` (with validation)\n- **Utility**: `close(): Promise<void>` for connection pool cleanup\n\nExamples:\n```typescript\ninsertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>;\ngetRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\ngetRoundsByPhase(phase: RoundPhase): Promise<Round[]>;\ngetUnsettledStats(): Promise<{ count: number; oldestAgeSeconds: number }>;\n```\n\n### 4. Key Query Patterns\n\n**RETURNING * pattern** (get fresh rows after mutation):\n```typescript\nINSERT INTO rounds (...) VALUES (...) RETURNING *\nUPDATE rounds SET ... WHERE pda = ${pda} RETURNING *\nDELETE FROM rounds WHERE pda = ${pda} RETURNING pda\n```\n\n**JSON/JSONB handling** with `sql.json()` helper:\n```typescript\n${params.entries ? sql.json(params.entries) : null}\n// or for updates\nentries = ${sql.json(entries)},\n```\n\n**COALESCE for partial updates** (merge provided values with existing):\n```typescript\ntarget_slot = COALESCE(${updates?.target_slot ?? null}, target_slot),\nsettle_attempts = COALESCE(${updates?.settle_attempts ?? null}, settle_attempts),\n```\n\n**Bulk insert pattern** using `sql(values, ...columns)`:\n```typescript\nconst values = params.map(p => ({...}));\nINSERT INTO transactions ${sql(values, \"wallet\", \"game\", \"match_id\", ...)}\nON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n```\n\n**Type-safe queries** with generic `sql<Type[]>`:\n```typescript\nconst rows = await sql<Round[]>`SELECT ...`;\nconst rows = await sql<{ count: string; oldest_age_seconds: string | null }[]>`SELECT ...`;\n```\n\n### 5. Type Definitions Pattern\n**Two-layer types**: Input parameters (camelCase) + Output rows (snake_case)\n\n**Input types**:\n```typescript\nexport interface InsertRoundParams {\n  pda: string;\n  game: string;\n  serverKey: string;  // camelCase input\n  amountLamports: number;\n  entries?: Array<{ player: string; amountLamports: number }>;\n}\n```\n\n**Output types** (match database schema):\n```typescript\nexport interface Round {\n  pda: string;\n  game: string;\n  server_key: string;  // snake_case from DB\n  amount_lamports: number;\n  entries: unknown | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n```\n\n### 6. Normalization Functions\n**Pattern**: Post-query normalization for type coercion (especially numeric/JSONB fields):\n```typescript\nfunction normalizeRound(row: Round): Round {\n  return {\n    ...row,\n    amount_lamports: Number(row.amount_lamports),\n    side: Number(row.side),\n    settle_attempts: Number(row.settle_attempts),\n    entries: Array.isArray(row.entries)\n      ? (row.entries as Array<{ player: string; amountLamports: number }>).map((e) => ({\n          player: e.player,\n          amountLamports: Number(e.amountLamports),\n        }))\n      : null,\n  };\n}\n```\n- Converts `string` numbers to proper `Number` type\n- Parses JSONB array entries and normalizes nested object shapes\n- Called on every query result before returning\n\n### 7. State Machine Pattern\n**Phase transitions** with validation:\n```typescript\nconst VALID_TRANSITIONS: Record<RoundPhase, readonly RoundPhase[]> = {\n  created: [\"locked\", \"expired\"],\n  locked: [\"settling\"],\n  settling: [\"settled\"],\n  settled: [],\n  expired: [],\n};\n\nfunction assertPhaseTransition(from: RoundPhase, to: RoundPhase): void {\n  const allowed = VALID_TRANSITIONS[from];\n  if (!allowed.includes(to)) {\n    throw new Error(`Invalid phase transition: ${from} → ${to}`);\n  }\n}\n```\n- Called inside `updateRoundPhase()` before executing SQL\n\n### 8. Error Handling\n**Explicit row existence checks**:\n```typescript\nconst current = await sql<Pick<Round, \"phase\">[]>`SELECT phase FROM rounds WHERE pda = ${pda}`;\nif (current.length === 0) {\n  throw new Error(`Round not found: ${pda}`);\n}\n```\n- Throws descriptive errors when expected rows are missing\n\n### 9. Special Features\n\n**Idempotent insert** with `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`:\n```typescript\nINSERT INTO transactions (...) VALUES (...) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n```\n- Used for transactions to prevent duplicate-key failures\n\n**Conditional query branching**:\n```typescript\nif (cursor && game) {\n  const rows = await sql<Transaction[]>`WHERE wallet = ${wallet} AND id < ${cursor} AND game = ${game}`;\n} else if (cursor) {\n  const rows = await sql<Transaction[]>`WHERE wallet = ${wallet} AND id < ${cursor}`;\n} else if (game) {\n  // ...\n}\n```\n- Different query paths based on optional parameters\n\n**Distinct ON for batch lookups**:\n```typescript\nSELECT DISTINCT ON (pda) * FROM operator_events\nWHERE pda = ANY(${pdas}) AND event_type = ${eventType}\nORDER BY pda, id DESC\n```\n- Returns latest event per PDA in single query\n- Returns `Map<string, OperatorEvent>` for keyed lookup\n\nAll of these patterns follow a **contract-first, type-safe, parameterized** approach with strong validation at the DB layer."}],"totalDurationMs":21520,"totalTokens":45049,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13146,"cache_read_input_tokens":30172,"output_tokens":1726,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13146},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
